  {title: "Part 1", description: "(1923-1998) was a Cuban revolutionary, academic, statesman and public figure. He was a captain who fought in the mountains alongside Che Guevara. After the revolution he was director of the National Institute of Agrarian Reform (INRA), which played a very significant role in the socialist transformation of Cuba. As Castro told the Soviets in 1960, INRA would achieve “the step-by-step elimination of property.” Nunez Jimeniz succeeded Guevara as president of the Cuban National Bank, and later was president of the Academy of Sciences, as well as serving for a time as Ambassador to Peru. Dr. Nunez Jimenez was one of Fidel Castro's closest friends.", duration: "00:08:51", film_id: 1, embed: "<iframe src=\"https://dev-dl-pa.home.nyu.edu/media/clips/TAM-616_ref108_000001/mode/embed/\" height=\"350\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>", collection_id: 1, slug: "antonio-nunez-jimenez-part-1", thumbnail_file_name: "1430314848.jpg", thumbnail_content_type: "image/jpeg", thumbnail_file_size: 42356, thumbnail_updated_at: "2015-04-30 01:17:04", name: "Antonio Nunez Jimenez ", transcript_file_name: nil, transcript_content_type: nil, transcript_file_size: nil, transcript_updated_at: nil, year: "May 29,1996", refid: "108_000001"},
