  {title: "Part 1", description: "<p>(1927-2009) was an important figure in the Cuban Revolution and later a Cuban official. The only Afro-Cuban to participate in the attack on the Moncada Barracks in 1953, Almeida was later among the small group (16 out of 82) to survive the initial battle after the landing of the Granma in 1956 and go into the mountains. He then commanded the Third Front. During the US-sponsored Bay of Pigs operation in April 1961, Almeida commanded the Cuban military&rsquo;s Central Army. Later a prominent figure in the Communist Party of Cuba, Almeida at the time of his death, was Vice-President of the Cuban Council of State and its third ranking member.</p>\r\n", duration: "00:28:53", film_id: 1, embed: "<iframe src=\"https://dev-dl-pa.home.nyu.edu/media/clips/TAM-616_ref893/mode/embed/\" height=\"350\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>", collection_id: 1, slug: "juan-almeida-bosque-part-1", thumbnail_file_name: "1430317562.jpg", thumbnail_content_type: "image/jpeg", thumbnail_file_size: 33496, thumbnail_updated_at: "2015-04-30 01:17:14", name: "Juan Almeida Bosque", transcript_file_name: nil, transcript_content_type: nil, transcript_file_size: nil, transcript_updated_at: nil, year: "June 5, 1997", refid: "893"},
