  {title: "Part 9", description: "<p>(1923-1998) was a Cuban revolutionary, academic, statesman and public figure. He was a captain who fought in the mountains alongside Che Guevara. After the revolution he was director of the National Institute of Agrarian Reform (INRA), which played a very significant role in the socialist transformation of Cuba. As Castro told the Soviets in 1960, INRA would achieve &quot;the step-by-step elimination of property.&quot; Nunez Jimeniz succeeded Guevara as president of the Cuban National Bank, and later was president of the Academy of Sciences, as well as serving for a time as Ambassador to Peru. Dr. Nunez Jimenez was one of Fidel Castro&#39;s closest friends.</p>\r\n", duration: "00:06:10", film_id: 1, embed: "<iframe src=\"https://dev-dl-pa.home.nyu.edu/media/clips/TAM-616_ref908/mode/embed/\" height=\"350\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>", collection_id: 1, slug: "antonio-nunez-jimenez-1923-1998-part-9", thumbnail_file_name: "1430317917.jpg", thumbnail_content_type: "image/jpeg", thumbnail_file_size: 42062, thumbnail_updated_at: "2015-04-30 01:17:15", name: "Antonio Nunez Jimenez", transcript_file_name: nil, transcript_content_type: nil, transcript_file_size: nil, transcript_updated_at: nil, year: "May 29,1996", refid: "908"},
