  {title: "Part 1", description: "<p>(1925-2013) was a lifelong friend of Fidel Castro. They were students at the University of Havana, where Guevara was a member of the Communist Youth organization. In 1947 Guevara and Castro ran against each other for secretary of the University&#39;s Student Federation (FEU). Guevara won. After the Revolution, Guevara became vice minister of Culture and, at Castro&#39;s request, established the Cuban Institute for Arts and Cinematography (I.C.A.I.C.), which sponsored Cuba&#39;s state-funded cinema. After leaving the ICAIC 1982, he spent nine years as Cuban ambassador to the United Nations educational, scientific and cultural organization (UNESCO). Having founded the International Festival of New Latin American Cinema in Havana in 1979, Guevara remained its president until his death.</p>\r\n", duration: "00:09:50", film_id: 1, embed: "<iframe src=\"https://dev-dl-pa.home.nyu.edu/media/clips/TAM-616_ref997_000001/mode/embed/\" height=\"350\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>", collection_id: 1, slug: "alfredo-guevara-valdes-part-1", thumbnail_file_name: "1430318269.jpg", thumbnail_content_type: "image/jpeg", thumbnail_file_size: 31822, thumbnail_updated_at: "2015-04-30 01:17:17", name: "Alfredo Guevara Valdes", transcript_file_name: nil, transcript_content_type: nil, transcript_file_size: nil, transcript_updated_at: nil, year: "May 27, 1996", refid: "997_000001"},
